Drew	Langan	"2022-06-26 18:17:20"	"Substantive Law"	"Illinois Bar Review - W24 -1737"	"MBE CONSTITUTIONAL LAW"	"Essay ID 5320"	"Hello,I'm wondering if part 3 of essay 5320 is implicated by a change in the law after TransUnion v. Ramirez? I'm just curious when this essay came out/when the model answer was written. After TransUnion, I don't think this class could show concrete injury just because hackers came into possession of their information, but maybe I'm not appreciating the difference between this hypothetical state statute and the Fair Credit Reporting Act violation alleged in TransUnion?"	"Essay ID 5320 (Civ Pro/ConLaw)"	Essay		729714	1737	421616	170254	"0000-00-00 00:00:00"	"2022-06-27 18:17:40"	1	5320	"MBE CONSTITUTIONAL LAW"	0	"Lindsey Hallam"	"Hi Drew,  Article III standing requires a concrete injury, even in the context of a statutory violation. TransUnion LLC v. Ramirez, 141 S. Ct. 2190, ___ U.S. ___ (2021) (holding that defendant&rsquo;s violation of the Fair Credit Reporting Act alone was not a concrete injury for purposes of Article III standing unless the violation caused the plaintiff to suffer a real world injury). Here, there was a statutory violation, but the violation caused the man to suffer a real world injury in that data breaches of medical information cause significant harm to the individuals involved and the knowledge that someone has obtained your private and personal medical information is distressing, whether the information has been used or could be used in the future. So, here, it&rsquo;s not a violation of the statute alone, the man has suffered a concrete injury.  I hope this helps!  Lindsey    Drew Langan @ 2022-06-26 18:17:20 wrote:  Hello,  I'm wondering if part 3 of essay 5320 is implicated by a change in the law after TransUnion v. Ramirez? I'm just curious when this essay came out/when the model answer was written. After TransUnion, I don't think this class could show concrete injury just because hackers came into possession of their information, but maybe I'm not appreciating the difference between this hypothetical state statute and the Fair Credit Reporting Act violation alleged in TransUnion?"	"Anindita Dutta"
