Jenae	Longenecker	"2022-06-20 13:31:25"	"Substantive Law"	"Illinois Bar Review - W24 -1737"	"MBE CRIMINAL LAW"		"What does it mean for an accessory to be constructively present at the scene of a crime? (Appears in outline)"	"Principal in the second degree "	General		724825	1737	345376	159137	"2022-06-21 09:56:50"	"2022-06-20 22:30:05"	1	0	"MBE CRIMINAL LAW"	0	"Steve Blum"	"Hi Jenae!  The principal in the second degree did not need to be actually present at the commission of the crime if she was aiding the principal and was close enough to render assistance if needed.The actor's constructive presence implicated her as long as she played an active role in the crime, such as being either a lookout or a driver of the getaway car, for example.  Hope this helps.  Steve    Jenae Longenecker @ 2022-06-20 13:31:25 wrote:  What does it mean for an accessory to be constructively present at the scene of a crime? (Appears in outline)"	"Lindsey Hallam"
