Jenae	Longenecker	"2022-06-19 23:20:03"	"Substantive Law"	"Illinois Bar Review - W24 -1737"	"MBE EVIDENCE"	4137	"For the voice ID issue, why is it permissible that the police officer testify about what the victim said? Yes, the victim is a witness who can be cross-examined, but shouldn't the victim be the one testifying to what he heard?"	"Hearsay exclusion"	Essay		724423	1737	345376	170254	"0000-00-00 00:00:00"	"2022-06-19 23:21:21"	1	4137	"MBE EVIDENCE"	0	"Lindsey Hallam"	"Hi Jenae,  FRE 801(d)(1)(C) does not require that the witness providing the foundation testimony to the fact the statement was made be the declarant of the statement; anyone who heard the statement may so testify, so long as the declarant is subject to cross-examination.  I hope this helps!  Lindsey    Jenae Longenecker @ 2022-06-19 23:20:03 wrote:  For the voice ID issue, why is it permissible that the police officer testify about what the victim said? Yes, the victim is a witness who can be cross-examined, but shouldn't the victim be the one testifying to what he heard?"	"Lindsey Hallam"
