Ty	Zhang	"2022-06-02 23:24:04"	"Substantive Law"	"Illinois Bar Review - W24 -1737"	"MBE REAL PROPERTY"		"Can you give me an example of how RAP is applied to rights of first refusals and options?"	"RAP and Right of First Refusal and Options"	General		711637	1737	421938	369848	"2022-06-05 15:59:07"	"2022-06-03 09:05:20"	1	0	"MBE REAL PROPERTY"	0	"Pamela Prieto"	"Hi Ty,  Example: The landlord made a lease agreement ""to B for 30 years, with an optionto acquire the property, then to C, for 30 years,with an optionto acquire the property, then to D for 30 years, with an optionto acquire the property.""  The RAP does not apply to an option to purchase the property or a right offirst refusal that is held by a current leasehold tenant. Thus, B's option is valid even if there is a possibility that he does not use the option within 21 years. However, C's and D's options violate RAP.The same example would also work for a right of first refusal.  Also, the RAP also does not apply to an option contract or a right of first refusal when the property right is created in a commercial transaction.  Hope this clarifies things!  Best,  Pam    Ty Zhang @ 2022-06-02 23:24:04 wrote:  Can you give me an example of how RAP is applied to rights of first refusals and options?"	"Dena Ray (Ed)"
