Molly	Skjerven	"2022-05-31 18:18:21"	"Substantive Law"	"Illinois Bar Review - W24 -1737"	"WILLS AND DECEDENTS' ESTATES"		"What is the difference between an administrator/executor and a donee? It sounds like they are both responsible for distributing the property of the estate."	"What's the difference? "	General	8	709585	1737	416239	170254	"0000-00-00 00:00:00"	"2022-05-31 18:26:12"	1	0	"WILLS AND DECEDENTS' ESTATES"	0	"Lindsey Hallam"	"Hi Molly,  An administrator is the person appointed by the court to be the executor of the will when the executor hasn&rsquo;t been specified or is unavailable. The executor is the person named in the will. A personal representative is either named in the will (executor) or appointed by the court (administrator) to oversee the winding up of a decedent&rsquo;s affairs. A donee is the person given the power of appointment. A power of appointment describes the ability of the testator (donor) to select an individual (donee) who may be given the authority to dispose of certain property under the will, similar to an agent. Overall, the duties are the same &ndash; disposing of the decedent&rsquo;s property.  I hope this helps!  Lindsey    Molly Skjerven @ 2022-05-31 18:18:21 wrote:  What is the difference between an administrator/executor and a donee? It sounds like they are both responsible for distributing the property of the estate."	"Anindita Dutta"
