Alana	Jones	"2022-05-26 11:08:35"	"Substantive Law"	"Illinois Bar Review - W24 -1737"	"MBE REAL PROPERTY"		"I am kind of confused about the concept of ""privity""?I understand it is an exchange to a subsequent owner, but will property owners be in privity if they give the subsequent owner the property by deed or gift? Or does it just refer to the original owner selling or transferring the land to another?"	Privity	General		706315	1737	420384	283716	"2022-05-30 21:05:40"	"2022-05-26 15:16:58"	1	0	"MBE REAL PROPERTY"	0	"Timothy Chessher"	"Hi Alana,    Horizontal privity - This means that there must be some shared property interest between the original parties, apart from the covenant itself. This is generally seen in a grantor-grantee, landlord-tenant, mortgagor-mortgagee relationship. There is not horizontal privity when two adjoining landowners merely make an agreement, unless there is a simultaneous grant of an interest (eg, adjoining landowners each granted to the other a right of access over his property for a road).     Vertical privity - This means there is an unbroken chain of ownership from the original parties, transferring the entirety of the interest of the covenanting party. There is not vertical privity if a covenanting party conveys a life estate interest in his property. The covenant cannot be enforced against the life tenant because a life tenant does not hold the entire FSA interest of the covenanting party.     Hope this helps. If not or if you have a question on a type of privity or a sample question, please send a follow-up message, and I will be happy to provide an additional response. Keep up the good work!    Best,          Timothy    Alana Jones @ 2022-05-26 11:08:35 wrote:  I am kind of confused about the concept of ""privity""?    I understand it is an exchange to a subsequent owner, but will property owners be in privity if they give the subsequent owner the property by deed or gift? Or does it just refer to the original owner selling or transferring the land to another?"	"Anindita Dutta"
